WEBVTT

00:01.836 --> 00:03.542
NARRATOR: "Previously on Teen Wolf..."

00:03.713 --> 00:05.999
- JACKSON: What's in here?
- Everything you want.

00:07.091 --> 00:08.956
I mean, the bus driver that got killed,

00:09.177 --> 00:11.668
the video store clerk
who got his throat slashed,

00:11.888 --> 00:13.674
they're all connected
to the Hale house fire.

00:13.890 --> 00:15.380
- (WHISTLING SOUND)
- Cover your eyes!

00:16.392 --> 00:18.849
(RAPID GUNFIRE)

00:20.188 --> 00:21.268
(ROARS)

00:21.689 --> 00:22.644
(GASPS)

00:22.857 --> 00:23.892
(COUGHING)

00:24.108 --> 00:25.723
I wouldn't get up just yet.

00:25.943 --> 00:27.319
But you're a vet.

00:27.570 --> 00:29.731
You know how every family
has its secrets?

00:30.156 --> 00:32.397
Ours are a little different.

00:33.576 --> 00:34.816
(ROARING)

00:37.371 --> 00:39.828
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

00:47.840 --> 00:50.297
(ELECTRONIC SIZZLING)

00:57.725 --> 00:59.386
(SCREAMS)

01:01.354 --> 01:03.970
ALLISON: "What are you doing to him?
Is that gonna kill him?"

01:04.941 --> 01:07.683
KATE: "Oh, come on, kiddo.
Don't get all ethical on me now."

01:07.902 --> 01:09.187
(SCREAMING)

01:09.946 --> 01:10.935
What is he?

01:11.155 --> 01:13.191
Shape-shifter. Lycan.

01:13.407 --> 01:15.113
Werewolf. (LAUGHING)

01:15.326 --> 01:17.942
To me, he's just another dumb animal.

01:22.458 --> 01:23.994
KATE: Come here.

01:24.210 --> 01:25.495
See these right here?

01:25.711 --> 01:29.203
These are canines,
also known as fangs.

01:29.423 --> 01:32.381
Made for the tearing and rending of flesh.

01:32.593 --> 01:36.006
Not something you'd find on those cute
little leaf-eating herbivores, is it?

01:36.222 --> 01:37.553
This is a joke to you?

01:37.765 --> 01:40.552
Sweetheart, there are werewolves
running around in the world.

01:41.602 --> 01:43.638
"Everything's a joke to me."

01:43.938 --> 01:46.350
"How else do you think I stay sane?"

01:46.691 --> 01:50.730
ALLISON: "So, it was him at the high school
and all the other animal attacks?"

01:51.988 --> 01:53.649
There's actually three of them.

01:53.823 --> 01:56.405
Another younger one like him
called the Beta,

01:56.617 --> 01:57.948
and then there's the Alpha.

01:58.160 --> 01:59.696
"Alpha's the pack leader."

01:59.912 --> 02:02.654
Bigger, stronger, nastier.

02:03.165 --> 02:05.827
Those are the real ugly mother...

02:06.419 --> 02:08.831
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

02:09.046 --> 02:10.252
(SIREN WAlLlNG)

02:10.464 --> 02:12.329
Oh, God, not now.

02:19.765 --> 02:22.381
When were they gonna tell me?

02:22.602 --> 02:25.139
They still haven't decided
if they're gonna tell you.

02:25.730 --> 02:26.685
ALLISON: "Why?"

02:26.856 --> 02:29.973
Let's just say if you react badly
when you find out...

02:30.192 --> 02:32.057
Not good.

02:32.278 --> 02:33.859
What do you mean, "Not good"?

02:34.071 --> 02:35.811
They don't think that you can handle it.

02:36.032 --> 02:38.193
They look at you
and they see this frightened little girl

02:38.409 --> 02:42.118
who's gonna run crying in the corner
when she finds out the truth.

02:42.330 --> 02:44.195
Me? What do I see?

02:44.415 --> 02:46.747
Natural talent.

02:46.959 --> 02:50.793
Allison, you said
you wanted to feel more powerful, right?

02:51.714 --> 02:53.170
Now's your chance.

02:53.382 --> 02:55.589
(SIREN WAlLlNG)

02:57.887 --> 03:00.003
ALLISON:
"What am I supposed to do now?"

03:00.222 --> 03:02.213
KATE:
"Go to school, do your homework."

03:02.433 --> 03:04.014
Go to the formal on Friday night.

03:04.226 --> 03:07.559
Be a normal teenage girl
who doesn't know anything.

03:07.772 --> 03:10.434
"Trust me to get everything ready
for the next part."

03:10.650 --> 03:12.311
What's the next part?

03:13.194 --> 03:15.651
You're gonna help me
catch the second Beta.

03:18.658 --> 03:20.148
(TAPPING)

03:28.793 --> 03:29.873
Allison?

03:31.087 --> 03:32.452
You all right?

03:33.005 --> 03:34.245
Yeah.

03:35.675 --> 03:39.759
Sorry I was going so fast,
I didn't realize I... l...

03:39.970 --> 03:41.710
(WHIMPERS)

03:41.889 --> 03:44.926
Oh, no. Uh... Okay, all right.

03:45.643 --> 03:47.383
Listen, you weren't going that fast.

03:47.603 --> 03:50.219
Just 75 in a 25,

03:50.439 --> 03:53.101
in a construction zone.

03:54.568 --> 03:56.980
I'm not crying to get out of the ticket.
ljust, um...

03:57.196 --> 03:58.436
I don't want you to think I'm like this.

03:58.656 --> 04:01.022
No, it's okay, perfectly okay. It's...

04:01.242 --> 04:04.359
No, please, write me a ticket.

04:04.578 --> 04:06.830
I need you to write me a ticket, okay?

04:08.374 --> 04:11.787
Okay. I don't see how that's gonna really
make you feel a lot better.

04:11.961 --> 04:15.249
It's so humiliating. I swear I'm not like this.

04:16.424 --> 04:17.960
- I understand.
- This isn't me.

04:18.175 --> 04:21.133
This is... This is... This is not me!

04:24.849 --> 04:26.464
This is not me.

04:30.020 --> 04:31.351
Uh-huh.

04:32.064 --> 04:33.600
I'm okay. (CLEARS THROAT)

04:33.816 --> 04:36.398
- Yeah?
- Yeah. I'm okay. I'm okay.

04:38.320 --> 04:40.811
Do I still have to write you a ticket?

04:41.198 --> 04:42.654
(EXHALES)

04:43.284 --> 04:45.741
(EXCITING MUSIC)

05:00.593 --> 05:02.174
(ARROW WHISTLING)

05:26.786 --> 05:30.119
Welcome back to the land of the conscious.
You doing okay?

05:30.873 --> 05:31.862
(CHUCKLES)

05:32.041 --> 05:34.202
Maybe you should sit down, huh?

05:34.418 --> 05:36.534
(BELL JINGLES)

05:36.754 --> 05:37.994
Hello?

05:38.214 --> 05:39.704
(DOOR CLOSES)

05:44.428 --> 05:46.339
I'm sorry, but we're...

05:47.473 --> 05:49.054
We're closed.

05:49.266 --> 05:51.097
Hi there. I'm here to pick up.

05:52.269 --> 05:54.976
I'm not sure I remember you dropping off.

05:56.732 --> 05:59.018
This one wandered in on its own.

05:59.944 --> 06:02.981
Even if he did, I'm afraid I can't help you.
We're closed.

06:03.405 --> 06:06.863
I think you can make an exception
this one time.

06:07.034 --> 06:08.319
Don't you?

06:09.036 --> 06:11.652
I'm sorry. That's not going to be possible.

06:12.414 --> 06:14.871
Maybe you could come back
during regular hours.

06:18.420 --> 06:20.206
You have something of mine.

06:22.174 --> 06:24.210
I'm here to collect it.

06:25.010 --> 06:26.750
Like I said,

06:29.139 --> 06:30.720
we're closed.

06:34.186 --> 06:36.598
(SOFT STATIC SIZZLE)

06:41.360 --> 06:42.975
(STATIC SIZZLING)

06:50.536 --> 06:52.743
Mountain ash.

06:52.955 --> 06:54.911
That's an old one.

07:01.964 --> 07:04.455
Let me be as clear as possible.

07:05.301 --> 07:06.416
We

07:06.802 --> 07:08.258
are

07:08.721 --> 07:10.427
closed.

07:23.485 --> 07:26.977
There are others
who can help me get what I want, Scott.

07:27.197 --> 07:29.108
"More innocent"

07:29.325 --> 07:31.782
"and far more vulnerable."

07:32.578 --> 07:33.567
Allison!

07:34.663 --> 07:36.574
(DOOR BELL JINGLES)

07:42.046 --> 07:43.286
Call it again.

07:43.505 --> 07:45.211
It's not here.

07:46.425 --> 07:47.665
So you lost your phone.

07:47.885 --> 07:49.295
Why don't you just get a new one?

07:49.511 --> 07:51.217
I can't afford a new one.

07:51.430 --> 07:53.671
And I can't do this alone.
We have to find Derek.

07:53.891 --> 07:56.758
Well, A, you're not alone. You have me.

07:57.645 --> 08:00.682
And B, didn't you say Derek walked
into gunfire? He sounds pretty dead.

08:00.898 --> 08:03.310
Argent's plan was to use him to get
the Alpha. They're not gonna kill him.

08:03.525 --> 08:06.016
All right, so then just let them do
what they're planning, you know?

08:06.195 --> 08:08.561
They use Derek to get Peter,
problem solved.

08:08.781 --> 08:11.443
Not if Peter's going after Allison
to find Derek!

08:11.659 --> 08:13.570
I can't protect her on my own.

08:13.786 --> 08:16.152
Which means we need to find Derek first.

08:16.372 --> 08:18.033
Just... Just help me!

08:18.791 --> 08:21.248
You know, you probably lost it
when you two were fighting.

08:21.460 --> 08:23.291
You remember that,
when he was trying to kill you?

08:23.504 --> 08:25.665
After you interrupted him
trying to kill Jackson?

08:25.881 --> 08:28.497
Are you starting
to see a pattern of violent behavior here?

08:28.717 --> 08:31.424
He wasn't going to kill anyone.

08:32.554 --> 08:34.806
And I'm not letting him die.

08:35.015 --> 08:37.597
Could you at least think
about letting him die?

08:37.810 --> 08:38.765
For me?

08:38.936 --> 08:40.346
(CAR APPROACHING)

08:40.562 --> 08:41.847
What?

08:42.064 --> 08:44.146
My mom just got home from work.

08:45.275 --> 08:47.357
Hi. It's me.

08:47.778 --> 08:50.360
Melissa McCall. Um...

08:50.572 --> 08:52.437
Giving you a call.
(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)

08:52.658 --> 08:55.195
That always sounds really weird
because of my last name. McCall.

08:55.411 --> 08:57.493
So, yeah.

08:58.080 --> 08:59.365
(ECHOING)
"You know, I was just wondering"

08:59.581 --> 09:02.709
"if maybe you wanted
to reschedule dinner or lunch."

09:02.918 --> 09:04.704
"No, it doesn't have to be dinner.
Lunch is good."

09:04.920 --> 09:07.081
"Or maybe you would like to do coffee,"

09:07.256 --> 09:08.666
"or maybe you're a tea drinker.
I don't know."

09:08.882 --> 09:11.214
"You know,
we could also just go out for drinks."

09:12.177 --> 09:15.544
Yeah, 'cause I think I need a few after this
profoundly embarrassing phone call.

09:15.764 --> 09:18.380
So if this really doesn't freak you out
too much,

09:18.600 --> 09:23.014
after this disastrous call,
feel free to give me a call.

09:26.817 --> 09:28.182
Is she okay?

09:31.405 --> 09:32.861
What's she doing?

09:34.491 --> 09:35.742
Crying.

09:36.785 --> 09:39.242
(SNIFFLING)

09:51.341 --> 09:54.048
Scott, you can't protect everyone.

09:56.055 --> 09:57.636
l have to.

09:59.058 --> 10:01.549
Come on, Derek. He killed your sister.

10:02.144 --> 10:04.476
Now, either you're not telling me

10:04.688 --> 10:07.430
because, well,
you want to kill him yourself,

10:08.150 --> 10:10.937
or, for some reason,

10:12.321 --> 10:14.061
you're protecting him.

10:18.202 --> 10:19.942
(CHUCKLES)

10:20.788 --> 10:22.744
Look at that sour face.

10:24.500 --> 10:26.991
I bet you always used to get people
coming up to you saying,

10:27.211 --> 10:30.703
"Smile, Derek. Why don't you smile more?"

10:31.632 --> 10:35.295
Don't you just want
to kick those people in the face?

10:37.137 --> 10:38.422
I can think of one.

10:40.265 --> 10:41.880
Promise?

10:42.768 --> 10:45.475
'Cause if I thought you'd be that much fun,

10:45.687 --> 10:47.348
I'll let you go.

10:48.816 --> 10:50.306
(SIGHING)

10:52.528 --> 10:54.644
All right, let's see.

10:54.863 --> 10:58.105
Nothing, nothing, nothing.
God, I hate this detective crap.

10:58.283 --> 11:01.525
Are you gonna torture me,
or are you just gonna talk me to death, huh?

11:04.665 --> 11:06.371
Oh, sweetie, I don't...

11:06.583 --> 11:08.665
I don't wanna torture you.

11:09.545 --> 11:12.002
ljust want to catch up.

11:12.631 --> 11:15.919
(GIGGLES)
Remember all the fun we had together?

11:16.135 --> 11:19.343
- Like the time you burned my family alive?
- (CHUCKLES)

11:19.555 --> 11:22.547
No, l was thinking more about the...

11:23.392 --> 11:26.600
hot, crazy sex we had.

11:27.729 --> 11:29.344
But the fire thing, yeah, that was fun, too.

11:29.565 --> 11:31.055
(LAUGHS)

11:31.275 --> 11:33.516
I love how much you hate me.

11:33.735 --> 11:35.020
(DEREK BREATHING HEAVILY)

11:35.237 --> 11:37.694
Remember how this felt?

11:40.909 --> 11:42.240
(ROARS)

11:46.123 --> 11:49.786
Mmm, sweetheart, I really don't want
to torture you.

11:50.294 --> 11:52.751
(METAL CLANKING)

11:57.843 --> 11:59.549
But he does.

11:59.761 --> 12:01.888
(CRACKING KNUCKLES)

12:49.394 --> 12:51.350
(THUD)

12:51.563 --> 12:53.303
SCOTT: Ow!

12:57.236 --> 12:58.772
(INDISTINCT TALKING)

12:58.987 --> 13:00.852
What do you mean,
I can't go to the formal?

13:01.073 --> 13:03.610
McCall, you're failing my class
and two others.

13:03.825 --> 13:05.326
They told me to cut you from the team.

13:05.494 --> 13:09.328
I told them I'd sooner cutoff
my last remaining testicle

13:09.498 --> 13:11.409
than cut my best player.

13:11.625 --> 13:15.038
So the compromise is
I can't go to the dance?

13:15.754 --> 13:16.709
Yeah.

13:18.340 --> 13:20.046
Then I quit the team.

13:20.425 --> 13:22.290
(LAUGHS)

13:22.469 --> 13:23.879
No, you don't.

13:24.096 --> 13:27.554
And if you show up at the dance
and | see you there,

13:28.308 --> 13:30.594
I'm gonna drag you out by your teeth.

13:37.150 --> 13:39.357
You want me to take her to the formal.

13:39.528 --> 13:42.019
I don't want you to. I need you to.

13:42.698 --> 13:44.359
Screw you.

13:44.574 --> 13:46.485
You know what? Screw you, too.

13:46.702 --> 13:48.112
In fact, screw each other.

13:48.328 --> 13:50.410
Hey, you know he saved your life, right?

13:50.622 --> 13:52.533
He left me for dead.

13:52.749 --> 13:53.829
I got shot for you.

13:54.042 --> 13:56.704
Oh, yeah? Show me the bullet wound.

13:56.920 --> 13:58.581
You know it healed.

13:58.797 --> 14:01.630
- Mmm, convenient.
- Just do it for Allison, okay?

14:01.842 --> 14:05.334
She's in serious danger.
I'm talking around-the-clock danger.

14:05.512 --> 14:07.377
She needs someone to keep an eye on her
at the dance.

14:07.556 --> 14:09.592
Just have her dad do it, okay?

14:09.808 --> 14:11.093
He's the one actually equipped
to handle this.

14:11.310 --> 14:14.177
How am I supposed to do that
and keep him from finding out about me?

14:14.438 --> 14:16.520
Not my problem.

14:19.901 --> 14:22.153
You're her friend, too.

14:22.362 --> 14:23.351
You are.

14:23.530 --> 14:24.861
All that time that you spent with her
to get to me,

14:25.073 --> 14:28.110
you can't tell me that you didn't get
to know her and like her.

14:28.327 --> 14:29.783
It's Allison.

14:29.995 --> 14:32.031
It's impossible not to like her.

14:32.247 --> 14:35.535
You can't tell me
that you don't care if she gets hurt.

14:37.085 --> 14:38.416
What if I get hurt?

14:38.628 --> 14:39.879
Then it's worth it.

14:40.505 --> 14:41.961
Not to me.

14:45.052 --> 14:47.008
(EXHALES)

14:48.138 --> 14:50.424
Well, I shouldn't say I told you so.

14:51.266 --> 14:54.884
'Cause it's not strong enough.
How about I'm always right,

14:55.103 --> 14:57.515
and you should listen
to whatever I have to say

14:57.731 --> 15:01.724
and never disagree, ever, ever,
for the sake of your wolflihood?

15:01.943 --> 15:03.649
I'm not done.

15:04.696 --> 15:06.982
You're not done.

15:09.451 --> 15:11.157
One more thing.

15:12.829 --> 15:15.286
(LOW GROWLING)

15:20.879 --> 15:23.916
Hey, what time should I pick you up
for the dance tomorrow?

15:24.132 --> 15:25.463
Are you okay?

15:25.634 --> 15:27.590
Yeah, I'm great.
I'm just excited to go to the formal.

15:27.803 --> 15:30.465
With you. As friends. Just friends.

15:30.639 --> 15:32.254
Just... Just friends.

15:32.474 --> 15:34.931
(BOTH LAUGHING)

15:36.645 --> 15:39.307
Hey, don't worry. I'll still be there.

15:39.523 --> 15:42.060
SCOTT: I'm still going.
STILES: Is that such a good idea?

15:44.820 --> 15:45.900
Not yet.

15:46.113 --> 15:47.853
Do you have a suit?

15:48.073 --> 15:49.279
Not yet.

15:49.491 --> 15:52.608
Do you have a ticket to the formal?
A ride there?

15:52.994 --> 15:54.495
No. And no.

15:54.871 --> 15:58.739
So, you're gonna ride your bike to a dance
that you're not even allowed to go to

15:58.959 --> 16:01.450
without a date, a suit, or a way in

16:01.628 --> 16:05.246
with werewolves and werewolf hunters
all out to kick your little werewolf ass.

16:05.465 --> 16:06.796
Yeah. You gonna help me?

16:07.008 --> 16:08.589
Hell, yeah.

16:08.802 --> 16:12.420
Nothing's wrong,
ljust... l have a lot on my mind.

16:12.597 --> 16:14.303
You could smile, at least.

16:14.516 --> 16:16.882
Ever heard of the saying, "Never frown.

16:17.102 --> 16:19.559
"Someone could be falling in love
with your smile"?

16:20.397 --> 16:21.887
Smile, Allison.

16:22.107 --> 16:23.972
I'm buying you a dress.

16:24.192 --> 16:27.355
Have to admit as far as apologies go,
that's more than I expected.

16:27.571 --> 16:28.902
Excellent.

16:29.489 --> 16:31.275
But not as much as I'm going to ask.

16:31.491 --> 16:33.948
What? What's that supposed to mean?

16:34.161 --> 16:36.026
It means you're going to cancel

16:36.246 --> 16:38.988
on whatever dumb,
roided-up jock you said yes to

16:39.207 --> 16:41.823
and you're going to go
with somebody else.

16:42.043 --> 16:43.203
Who?

16:45.881 --> 16:46.916
Him.

16:49.134 --> 16:51.170
(SNEEZING)

16:51.386 --> 16:55.174
Oh... Don't frown, Lydia.

16:55.390 --> 16:58.598
Someone could be falling in love
with your smile.

17:05.150 --> 17:09.143
Okay, so are you just gonna
try these on right now?

17:09.362 --> 17:11.068
All of them?

17:11.281 --> 17:13.567
Is this a 24-hour Macy's?

17:31.927 --> 17:33.713
That's not your color.

17:34.471 --> 17:36.712
Sorry if that was intrusive,

17:36.932 --> 17:40.550
but considering your skin tone,
I'd go lighter.

17:41.269 --> 17:43.351
'Cause I'm pale?

17:43.563 --> 17:44.939
Fair.

17:45.732 --> 17:48.724
I mean, you can't call skin like yours pale.

17:48.944 --> 17:50.980
Not skin that perfect.

17:51.696 --> 17:53.027
Okay.

17:53.573 --> 17:58.909
Trust me,
l have a unique perspective on the subject.

17:59.120 --> 18:00.656
Do you mind?

18:05.460 --> 18:06.575
See?

18:07.963 --> 18:09.169
Much better.

18:16.555 --> 18:18.591
You're not here alone, are you?

18:20.642 --> 18:23.054
Shopping for dresses with friends.

18:27.107 --> 18:28.392
High school dance.

18:28.650 --> 18:30.641
- Formal.
- Oh.

18:33.655 --> 18:36.818
- "license plate 5UN I768."
- Did she just say a blue Mazda?

18:37.033 --> 18:40.241
- "Your car is being towed..."
- (GASPS) What? That's my car.

18:52.632 --> 18:54.133
l have to say, Scott,

18:54.342 --> 18:57.129
I continue to be impressed
with your ingenuity.

18:57.762 --> 18:59.548
Just remember.

19:00.348 --> 19:02.725
You can't be everywhere all the time.

19:07.188 --> 19:09.520
CHRIS: "Hey, it's me.
I'm getting tired of leaving messages."

19:09.733 --> 19:12.691
"I want to know where you are.
Call me. Now."

19:15.447 --> 19:20.658
(SIGHS) Unfortunately, Derek,
if you're not gonna talk,

19:20.827 --> 19:22.988
I'm just gonna have to kill you.

19:23.204 --> 19:26.241
So, say hi to your sister for me.

19:29.002 --> 19:31.539
You did tell her about me, didn't you?

19:31.755 --> 19:33.791
The truth about the fire?

19:35.175 --> 19:36.665
Or did you?

19:37.260 --> 19:38.636
(GASPS)

19:40.680 --> 19:42.762
(WHISPERS) Did you tell anybody?

19:43.767 --> 19:45.758
Oh, sweetie,

19:46.436 --> 19:48.597
that's just a lot of guilt to keep buried.

19:49.064 --> 19:51.976
It's not all your fault.
